{
  "text": "I may be backtracking a little bit and make a few false starts today because I think we are possibly the most important part of what we're doing, and that I'm trying to make it apparent through questioning how everything is one and how it comes from the one intelligent infinity. This is difficult for me to do, so please bear with my errors in questioning. The concept that I have right now of the process using both what you have told me and some of Dewey Larson's material having to do with the physics of the process, have the concept that intelligent infinity expands outward from all locations everywhere, expands outward in every direction, uniformly, like the surface of a balloon or bubble expanding outward from every point, everywhere. It expands outward at what's called unit velocity or the velocity of light. This is Larson's idea of the progression of what he calls space-time. Is this concept correct? I am wrong. This concept is incorrect as is any concept of the one intelligent infinity. This concept is correct in the context of one particular logos or love or a focus of this Creator which has chosen its, shall we say natural laws and ways of expressing them mathematically and otherwise the one undifferentiated intelligent infinity, unpolarized, full and whole is the macrocosm of the mystery clad being.",
